tr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wsr1665702720451.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wsr1665702720451.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wsr1665702720451.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wsr1665702720451\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the delay time for creating print files.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__topic_d142397e1_d142398e1_d142399e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__p_d142400e1_d142401e1_d142402e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PRT_FILE_DELAY</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DelayTimeMilliSecs</var></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__section_fhw_j3v_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464671e64\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__p_d142406e1_d142407e1_d142408e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">DelayTimeMilliSecs</var>—integer\n            ranging from 0 to 2000 (2 seconds)</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__section_vsx_n3v_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464671e75\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__table_d16646e1_d16647e1_d16648e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">client assignment files </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__section_lrw_q3v_jwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d464671e121\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wsr1665702720451__p_d142415e1_d142416e1_d142417e1\">On a FAT file system, use this assignment setting\n            to slow the pace of Uniface creating print files. It can happen that you write print\n            files so quickly (for instance, in a tight loop) that the write time of each file does\n            not change and the same file is repeatedly overwritten.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bsm1665702989373.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Files</a><p>A print file is created by Uniface using the specified print job model and print mode.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533513\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533513\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$PRT_FILE_DELAY Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Set the delay time for creating print files. $PRT_FILE_DELAY = DelayTimeMilliSecs Arguments DelayTimeMilliSecs —integer ranging from 0 to 2000 (2 seconds) Defaults Assignment file: client assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description On a FAT file system, use this assignment setting to slow the pace of Uniface creating print files. It can happen that you write print files so quickly (for instance, in a tight loop) that the write time of each file does not change and the same file is repeatedly overwritten. Related Links Print Files A print file is created by Uniface using the specified print job model and print mode. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}